  <p class="sec-body" id="weatherNote" style="margin-bottom:0">West Bengal has four seasons: winter (Nov–Feb), spring (Mar–Apr), monsoon (May–Oct) and a brief autumn. October to March is ideal — Durga Puja transforms every city in October, Darjeeling tea is harvested in spring, and Kolkata's cultural season peaks in winter. The Sundarbans is best visited November to March.</p>
